title: Scene04_Dialogue
---
Narrator: After following the guide of the nurse, Edmund finally arrives at the Archive's door.

Narrator: Inside, rows of medical drawers line the walls. Each bears a family crest, a patient number, and a wax seal.

Narrator: He spends some time before he can find the one marked:

Narrator: House Ashworth - Lord Edmund

Narrator: He opens it.

Edmund: There you are.

Narrator: He unfolds the paper.

Narrator: Edmund slowly touches his left shoulder.

Edmund: The West Wing...

Edmund: I remember the heat. The screaming pipes...

Edmund: ...And Father breaking the door open with his bare hands.

Edmund: 2:15 A.M.

Edmund: That was when the West Wing burned.

Narrator: He pulls his collar aside and looks at the scar.

Edmund: Same place. Same wound.

Edmund: But if he was made from me - remade from me - then he must carry it too.

Edmund: A scar proves the wound happened. Does not prove who it happened to.

Narrator: He folds the record anyway.

Edmund: It will have to be enough. For now.

Narrator: A lamp passes beyond the archive door. Edmund steps back into the shadow between the drawers.

Narrator: Two night-watchmen cross the hall outside, their boots slow against the tile.

Narrator: One of them pauses.

Narrator: Then the bell rings, far above. And with that, the footsteps move on.

Nurse: Did you find it?

Edmund: The first proof.

Nurse: My lord — that record was under the Court’s seal. If you present it, they will know how you came by it.

Edmund: Then they will know I was desperate.

Nurse: They may decide desperation is what a counterfeit looks like.

Edmund: ...Then may it be enough.

Narrator: He steps back into the fog, the medical record held tightly in his hand.

Narrator: The first proof has been found.

Narrator: Body Proof.

===
